HEADWORD: Opinionable
<hw>O*pin"ion*a*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Being, or
capable of being, a matter of opinion; that can be thought; not
positively settled; <as>as, an <ex>opinionable</ex> doctrine</as>.</def>
<rj><au>C. J. Ellicott.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Opinionate</ent>⟦br⟧
